Be reasonable; support ACTUAL artists who care about their craft instead of just their coin.

I definitely went on a tangent somewhere in this threat but the gist of what I'm saying is there's some artists who work really hard and don't get recognized for their work (NSFW artists), then there's artists known for their infamous works that get undeserved attention (NFT/Ken)

Ken claims the events that led to Scourge getting his chest SCAR was not canon, yet will accept the palette and name changes done in the same scene. Nitpicking canonical events isn't right. Much like it isn't right to sell outrageously priced pieces of near identical artwork; NFT

The sane goes for his rendition of Scourge. Ken claims he owns Scourge despite never referring to his character by that name. Scourge's name and green coloring comes from Ian's comics when he drops the name Evil Sonic after taking in the Master Emerald's power.

With that being said, my opinions shared here are not referring to exclusively NFT artists or the likes of Ken Penders who are greedy for money and willing to twist arms to fill their pockets. I am still appalled by Ken's attempt to claim he owns Shade in his NFT line of art.
--exclusively NSFW and not all SFW artists offer NSFW, but all art deserves to be respected and appreciated no matter how bad others think they are from time to time.

Art in and of itself is a finely honed talent which I support. While I typically try to avoid having NSFW content on my main account (I have a side account dedicated to sharing and supporting art), I still wish to put my voice out there in support. Not all artists are-- https://t.co/32o9suoNPj
